news.title: Adler overvalued real estate property by up to $239 million: Regulator
news.para: The Glasmacherviertel project to develop a former glassworks in Duesseldorf was valued at 375 million euros, and therefore overvalued by between 170 million and 233 million euros, the BaFin regulator said.

news.title: YEIDA to recover Rs 1,000 crore dues from industrial plot allottees in 15 days
news.para: Officials said these allottees have been issued recovery notices and asked to pay the difference amount along with interest in the next 15 days.

news.title: Can't levy commercial tax on renting out a residential building: Kerala HC
news.para: The petitioner had challenged the demand for higher tax by the revenue authorities by stating that renting out a residential building amounts to commercial activity.

news.title: Mumbai: SC grants Orbit Ventures Developers' directors interim relief from arrest
news.para: The two, Rajen Dhruv and Hiren Dhruv of Orbit Ventures Developers, had filed a special leave petition (SLP) for permission to challenge the Bombay high court orders of July 21-22 directing police to trace and arrest them so that they can be made to serve the term.

news.title: Eight-zone land use plan chalked out at Secunderabad cantonment board meet
news.para: Under the proposal vacant land would be earmarked as residential, commercial, mixed use zone, limited mixed use zone, zones for economically weaker sections, institutional area zone, green zone and Army/defence and government use zone.

news.title: Ajmera Realty's subsidiary acquires land in Mumbai for Rs 42.5 crore
news.para: The plot located at Pantnagar, Ghatkopar in Mumbai is owned by MHADA, while Tata Communication was the original lessee.

news.title: Coimbatore corporation zonal offices to issue building plan approval soon
news.para: When the issue of delay was taken up by north zone chairman V Kathirvel in the recent council meeting, corporation commissioner M Prathap said that assistant commissioners will be empowered to clear the plans if the area of construction is up to 1,500 square feet.

news.title: Gurugram: Builder to stop DG backup, Chintels Paradiso residents fret
news.para: Department of Town and Country Planning has asked 22 developers, including Chintels, to curb the use of DG sets as well as submit an action taken report by August 4.

news.title: Bengaluru: BMRCL in talks with three more firms to fund metro work
news.para: KIA Metro civil work between KR Puram and the Kempegowda International Airport is already progressing and is expected to be completed by 2025.

news.title: Kolkata civic body identifies 150 'extremely vulnerable' buildings for demolition
news.para: A communication in this regard has reached the KMC borough executive engineers from the civic headquarters, asking them to take immediate action to raze rickety buildings that might collapse in the event of incessant rain.

news.title: Brick kiln workers in Erode district stage protest
news.para: Several brick kilns are housed at Dasappagoundanpudur, Athipannagoundarpudur, Sathumugai and Kodiveri areas in Sathyamangalam taluk.

news.title: Chennai: 196 buildings on Mandaveli-Adyar metro route could be affected
news.para: A metro rail official said a survey had identified 119 such buildings between Mandaveli and Greenways Road, and 77 buildings between Greenways Road and Adyar junction.

news.title: Maharashtra meets just 12% of target under PMAY
news.para: Fadnavis said while the target was building 17 lakh homes in urban areas, only 12% was achieved. In sharp contrast PMAY (Rural) achieved 76% of its target.

news.title: Lucknow: Deposit house tax with 10% discount till August 31
news.para: The decision was taken by mayor Sanyukta Bhatia after witnessing heavy rush on LMC counters to take advantage of the discount on the last day on Sunday.

news.title: Complete housing programme on time: Andhra Pradesh CM
news.para: The officials told the chief minister that the construction work of houses in Visakhapatnam would start by the end of October 2022. They said that the tendering and other process has been completed here and the work is ready to start.
